cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.DB 

The paper discusses the application of deep learning techniques for spatio-temporal data mining, which involves machine learning and data mining tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep learning models such as CNN and RNN are commonly used in these fields. The paper also involves data management and retrieval, which suggests the possibility of cs.DB (Databases) being a relevant sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the applications of deep learning for various domains, which may suggest the possibility of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) being a relevant sub-category.
